cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CC 

The paper deals with network coding capacity and capacity regions, which are topics related to information theory and networking. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses matroidal networks, which are related to combinatorial optimization and graph theory, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper presents algorithms and heuristics for computing capacity regions, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
